title: Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill

heading_context: Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
chunks.html_content: You must pay your Simple Assessment tax bill if you’ve been sent a letter by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC).
chunks.plain_content:
Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
You must pay your Simple Assessment tax bill if you’ve been sent a letter by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC).

heading_context: Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
chunks.html_content: This guide is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).
chunks.plain_content:
Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
This guide is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).

heading_context: Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
Make an online payment
chunks.html_content:
You may get a Simple Assessment letter if you:

  • owe Income Tax that cannot be automatically taken out of your income
  • owe HMRC £3,000 or more
  • have to pay tax on the State Pension

If you think any information in the letter is wrong or you cannot pay your bill on time, you must contact HMRC within 60 days.

You’ll need your 14-character payment reference number starting with ‘X’ when you pay. You’ll find it on your Simple Assessment letter.

You can pay by:

  • approving a payment through your online bank account - you’ll be asked to sign in to your online bank account
  • debit or corporate credit card

heading_context: Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
Make an online payment
chunks.html_content: There’s a fee if you pay by corporate credit card or corporate debit card. The fee is not refundable.
chunks.plain_content:

There’s a fee if you pay by corporate credit card or corporate debit card. The fee is not refundable.

heading_context: Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
Make an online payment
chunks.html_content:
You cannot pay with a personal credit card.

If you choose to pay through your online bank account, you can either make an instant payment or select a date to pay. The date needs to be before your payment is due.

You’ll be asked if you want to sign in to your Personal Tax Account when you use the online service.

Signing in lets you see and pay tax you owe, but you can still pay without signing in.

heading_context: Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
Make a bank transfer
If you’re paying from a UK account
chunks.html_content:
You can pay using online banking or telephone banking, Faster Payments, CHAPS or Bacs.

It usually takes up to 3 working days for your payment to reach HMRC. Check your bank’s transaction limits and processing times before making a payment.

Pay into this account:

  • sort code - 08 32 10
  • account number - 12001020
  • account name - HMRC Shipley

heading_context: Pay your Simple Assessment tax bill
Send a cheque
chunks.html_content:
Write your 14-character payment reference number starting with ‘X’ on the back of the cheque - you’ll find it on your Simple Assessment letter.

It usually takes 3 working days for your payment to reach HMRC.
